<br>
I don't think any of us are debating the relative ease of this epic.  But, just because it's easy doesn't make it any less desirable.  As I'm sure you know, adding ONE epic to a guild allows them to try the harder stuff in the game, as they can risk more deaths.  It is significnatly easier to recover from a failure if there is a Epic-equipped cleric around.  Having the second cleric adds some level of security to those operations, especially if (when) the one cleric starts complaining about treated like a china-doll.<br>
<br>
Sure, every cleric wants the epic as it's a kick-ass item in its own right. But the effect on it is desired by your mates, who do not have instant personal access to a rez of their own.<br>
<br>
Personally, I'd not be surprised (or particularly annoyed) if they seriously mucked with the quest making it more difficult and adding an element on non-linearity once one has the swirling pearl. Something like travel hither and yon gathering these bits and if you give them to THIS guy (a daily spawn) he summons ragefire, who drops the heart-box. This spreads the clerics at this point out to hither and yon as they gather their bits from appropriately uncommon or rare mobs, and when thier group is ready for the fight - they go do the fight.  <br>
<br>
BUT - it is up to them to determine how much they're willing to do to change this...  they CAN say &quot;we like the current situation, as it fosters inter-player communication.&quot;<br>
