<br>
As to what constitutes failure - losing (getting wiped out) is failure, always has been.  If people are waiting and you fail, expect them to take their shot.<br>
<br>
As to Rage being triggered - this is silly.  The human form is a joke and can be done by one group easily.  I think he can probably be done by a bard solo given the number of charmable mobs around.  Killing the human doesnt mean anything in terms of &quot;who gets to kill ragefire.&quot;  If you spawn rage and your forces can't win the fight immediately, expect someone else to step in and take the spawn.  At the same time - kiting Rage to where the raid is gathered or while the raid (with forces in zone but not all in one place) gets to a location means that Ragefire is engaged.<br>
